cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the problem of spectrum shortage in UAV networks and proposes a spectrum sharing model to improve the QoS during disaster relief operations. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of UAVs for disaster relief missions and proposes an autonomous spectrum management scheme for the UAV network. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a model-free reinforcement learning algorithm for the UAVs to fine-tune their position and maximize their throughput and lifetime. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the security and privacy concerns related to spectrum sharing between the UAV network and terrestrial networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes a hierarchical mechanism for managing the operation of the UAV network.
